[[File:Benbros water cart.jpg|thumb|Benbros model of horse drawn water cart, circa 1959]] '''Benbros (London) Ltd''' was a British toy company in existence from the late 1940s<ref name=Ramsey>{{cite book|last=Ramsey|first=John|title=British Diecast Model Toys Catalogue|publisher=Swapmeet Publications|date=1995|page=21|isbn=0950931993}}</ref> to 1965.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fabtintoys.com/Benbros/|title=Benbros Ltd|website=fabtintoys|accessdate=5 March 2018}}</ref>
The company was founded by two brothers, Jack and Nathan Benenson,<ref name=Ramsey/> the name, a contraction of "Benenson Brothers", was adopted in 1951<ref name=Ramsey/> and the company was based at 145, Gosport Road, [[Walthamstow]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://homepage.ntlworld.com/d.jones7317/public_html/3index/benbros.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=21 October 2008|deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081024171034/http://homepage.ntlworld.com/d.jones7317/public_html/3index/benbros.htm |archivedate=24 October 2008 |df= }}</ref>
Benbros produced: * [[Die cast]] metal [[model car]]s and [[farm machinery]] under the names of "Qualitoys" and "T.V. Series" that came packed in a box that looked like a [[television]] set that were later retitled "Mighty Midgets". * "Zebra Toys" that came in black and white striped boxes that were better quality models.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.modelcollector.co.uk/content/a_z/z.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=21 October 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071101094410/http://www.modelcollector.co.uk/content/a_z/z.htm |archivedate=1 November 2007 |df= }}</ref> * [[Hollow casting|Hollow cast]] metal [[Robin Hood]], cowboy and Indian figures<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.knightsofavalon.com/beta_benbros_bmcl-wild-west.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=21 October 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080821042326/http://www.knightsofavalon.com/beta_benbros_bmcl-wild-west.htm |archivedate=21 August 2008 |df= }}</ref> and [[toy soldiers]].
[[Timpo]] Toys sold several of their moulds to Benbros, which can lead to collectors to having difficulty identifying which company made some figures.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.modelcollector.co.uk/content/a_z/t.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=21 October 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081005183648/http://www.modelcollector.co.uk/content/a_z/t.htm |archivedate=5 October 2008 |df= }}</ref>
