'''Los Aleros''' is a [[theme park]] located near [[Mérida, Mérida|Mérida]], [[Venezuela]]. It depicts a typical [[Andes|Andean]] town in the 1930s.<ref>Russell Maddicks, ''Bradt Travel Guide Venezuela'' ([[Bradt Travel Guides]], 2011), {{ISBN|978-1841622996}}, p. 370. [https://books.google.com/books?id=1pnZHGawJy0C&lpg=PA370&dq=%22los%20aleros%22&pg=PA370#v=onepage&q=%22los%20aleros%22&f=false Excerpts available] at [[Google Books]].</ref>  It was created by Alexis Montilla in 1984; he subsequently created the nearby "Venezuela de Antier" and "Montaña de los Sueños" themeparks.<ref>[http://www.eluniversal.com/2010/04/26/en_est2_apo_dreaming-of--the-ven_26A3780011.shtml "Dreaming of the Venezuela of the Day Before Yesterday"], ''[[El Universal (Caracas)|El Universal]]'', April 26, 2010.</ref><ref>[http://diariodelosandes.com/content/view/87800/105694/ "Los Aleros: un pueblo andino que nos lleva al pasado y sus tradiciones"], ''El Diario de los Andes'', July 28, 2009 (in Spanish).</ref><ref>Humberto Márquez, [http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-91087596.html "Venezuela: Film Industry Of Early Days Recalled In New Theme Park"], [[Inter Press Service]], February 13, 2004 {{subscription required|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}}.</ref>

